Dictionary.Name: The Collaborative International Dictionary of English v.0.44

Definition.WordDefinition:
Parlance \Par"lance\ (p[aum]r"lans), n. [OF., fr. F. parler to speak. See {Parley}.] Conversation; discourse; talk; diction; phrase; as, in legal parlance; in common parlance. [1913 Webster]
A hate of gossip parlance and of sway. --Tennyson. [1913 Webster]
parlance n : a manner of speaking that is natural to native speakers of a language [syn: {idiom}]
